preferred_name.label: Binary sensor technology, safety-related sensor technology

definition.text: technical sensor technology deals with technical products which transforms non-electronic measured variables into electrical signals. In many cases unitary signals or lately more and more field buses are applied in practice. The binary sensor technology takes a look at binary, i.e. switching systems which are used for the preservation of a state, which should be as free from dangers as possible, of a technical system. Main group 27270000 is structured based on sensors which function according to different principles, roughly structured in switches and keepers as well as according to the components, the accessories, briefing, training, maintenance, inspection and service of safety-related sensor technology

Controlling is the directed influence of the properties of a system from the outside by input. To that end information is to be transferred, processed and passed on via sensors. Main group 27240000 is divided into controlling devices of various function principles, control software and external devices (storage and field buses). Furthermore it is divided into parts, accessories, briefing, training, start-up, assembly, maintenance, inspection and service of control units

cable is defined as an interconnection of wires (conductors), coated with a shrouded insulation casing or optical conductors which fulfils a homogeneous cross-section profile. Cables transfer energy or information, they often contain further inner cladding layer consisting of insulating material. Wires consist of electrically conducting materials, e.g. copper or aluminium, they are part of an electrical circuit and connect the power source and the consumers. Main group 27060000 is structured according to the transported media energy, data and light waves as well as the combination of those media (hybrid cable). The media are furthermore divided according to size, form, use, special usage and packaging. Another differentiation is done according to components , accessories, inspection and service of cables and wires

electrical drive is a drive with an electrical engine which is operated by an automatic control. Electrical energy is converted into mechanical kinetic energy, thereof the reverse principle of the electrical generator applies. The resulting kinetic energy exists as linear or rotary movement. The efficiency factor, the relation from submitted to supplied power, continues to grow up to 99% with the increase of the power. Main group 27020000 is structured by the classification of the electric drives according to their function principle and the specification of the operating input energy and its transformation into other appropriate forms. Furthermore there is a differentiation between control electronics and regulation electronics in particular and the assembly, service, inspection and maintenance of the electric drives in general

a sensor can be installed flush if any restraining work substance/ material can be placed around the active surface without affecting its distinguishing characteriztics. A sensor cannot be installed flush if a certain free or open zone is required around its active surface. A sensor can be installed quasi-flush if its construction type allows for flush installation (and thus does not have the typical plastic cap of open zone sensors) but still have open zone switching states. these sensors are mostly not 100% flush or even over-flush installable, but need a small free or open zone (projecting length)
